# Dataset Architecture

## Three-Layer Design

The dataset system has **three complementary layers**:

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│              anno-core/src/dataset.rs                       │
│   DatasetSpec trait (interface) + CustomDataset (runtime)   │
│   Purpose: Extensibility, user-defined datasets             │
└─────────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────┘
                          │ implements
          ┌───────────────┴───────────────┐
          │                               │
┌─────────▼─────────┐          ┌──────────▼──────────┐
│ dataset_registry  │          │ User-defined        │
│ 184 built-in      │          │ CustomDataset       │
│ (define_datasets!)│          │ instances           │
└─────────┬─────────┘          └─────────────────────┘
          │
┌─────────▼─────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    loader.rs                       │
│   Download + Cache + Parse (188 variants)          │
│   Purpose: IO operations, checksums, caching       │
└───────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### Layer 1: `anno-core/src/dataset.rs` (Abstraction)

```rust
// Core trait - implement this for any dataset
pub trait DatasetSpec: Send + Sync {
    fn name(&self) -> &str;
    fn id(&self) -> &str;
    fn task(&self) -> Task;
    fn languages(&self) -> &[&str];
    fn entity_types(&self) -> &[&str];
    fn parser_hint(&self) -> ParserHint;
    fn license(&self) -> License;
    // ... optional methods with defaults
}
```

| Type | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `DatasetSpec` trait | Core interface all datasets implement |
| `CustomDataset` | Builder for runtime-defined datasets |
| `DatasetRegistry` | Runtime registry for custom datasets |

### Layer 2: `anno/src/eval/dataset_registry.rs` (Metadata)

The `define_datasets!` macro generates 184 built-in datasets with rich metadata:

```rust
define_datasets! {
    WikiGold {
        name: "WikiGold",
        description: "Wikipedia-based NER (2009)",
        url: "...",
        entity_types: ["PER", "LOC", "ORG", "MISC"],
        language: "en",
        domain: "news",
        license: "CC-BY-3.0",
        citation: "Balasuriya et al. (2009)",
        categories: [ner],
    },
    // ... 183 more
}
```

- Categories: `biomedical`, `literary`, `multilingual`, `low_resource`, etc.
- Tasks: `ner`, `coref`, `re`, `el`, `event_coref`, etc.
- Metadata: license, citation, paper_url, year, format, size_hint

### Layer 3: `anno/src/eval/loader.rs` (Operations)

Handles actual data loading:
- Download URLs with fallbacks
- SHA256 checksum verification  
- Persistent caching (`~/.cache/anno/`)
- Format-specific parsers (CoNLL, JSONL, BRAT, etc.)
- Graceful offline degradation

### Known Drift

The TODO at loader.rs:83-95 notes:
- `loader.rs`: 188 variants
- `dataset_registry.rs`: 184 variants
- Shared: only 62 variants

This drift means some datasets exist in one but not the other.

## Adding a New Dataset

### For runtime/custom datasets (preferred)

```rust
use anno_core::dataset::*;

let mahanama = CustomDataset::new("mahanama", Task::NED)
    .with_name("Mahānāma")
    .with_languages(&["sa"])
    .with_entity_types(&["Person", "Location", "Miscellaneous"])
    .with_parser(ParserHint::CoNLLU)
    .with_license(License::CCBY)
    .with_domain(Domain::Literary)
    .with_url("https://github.com/sujoysarkarai/mahanama")
    .with_secondary_tasks(vec![Task::IntraDocCoref, Task::NER])
    .with_stats(DatasetStats {
        doc_count: Some(2110),
        mention_count: Some(109_000),
        entity_count: Some(5_500),
        token_count: Some(988_502),
        split_sizes: Some(SplitSizes { train: 1688, dev: 211, test: 211 }),
    })
    .with_citation("Sarkar et al. (2025)")
    .historical();

let mut registry = DatasetRegistry::new();
registry.register(mahanama);
```

### For built-in datasets (requires both files)

1. Add to `define_datasets!` in `dataset_registry.rs`:

```rust
Mahanama {
    name: "Mahānāma",
    description: "Sanskrit EDL from Mahābhārata. Extreme name variation.",
    url: "https://github.com/sujoysarkarai/mahanama",
    entity_types: ["Person", "Location", "Miscellaneous"],
    language: "sa",
    domain: "literary",
    license: "CC-BY-4.0",
    citation: "Sarkar et al. (2025)",
    paper_url: "https://arxiv.org/abs/2509.19844",
    year: 2025,
    format: "CoNLLU",
    annotation_scheme: "Standoff",
    size_hint: "988K tokens, 109K mentions, 5.5K entities",
    notes: "124 avg name forms/entity. 47% ambiguity. 39% MWT mentions.",
    splits: ["train", "dev", "test"],
    tasks: ["ner", "coref", "el"],
    categories: [coref, literary, ancient, long_document, low_resource],
},
```

2. Add variant + URL to `DatasetId` in `loader.rs` (if loadable)
3. Add parser logic if new format
4. Run: `cargo test -p anno --features eval`

## Future: Bridging the Layers

The `DatasetSpec` trait could unify all three layers:

```rust
// Potential bridge (not yet implemented)
impl DatasetSpec for dataset_registry::DatasetId {
    fn name(&self) -> &str { self.name() }
    fn id(&self) -> &str { /* variant name */ }
    fn task(&self) -> Task { self.tasks().first().map(parse_task)? }
    fn languages(&self) -> &[&str] { &[self.language()] }
    fn entity_types(&self) -> &[&str] { self.entity_types() }
    fn parser_hint(&self) -> ParserHint { self.format().map(parse_format)? }
    fn license(&self) -> License { self.license().map(parse_license)? }
    // ...
}
```

This would allow using `DatasetId` wherever `DatasetSpec` is expected.

## Format Support

| ParserHint | Extensions | Example Datasets |
|------------|------------|------------------|
| `CoNLL` | .conll, .txt, .bio | CoNLL2003, WNUT17 |
| `CoNLLU` | .conllu | CorefUD, Mahānāma |
| `JSONL` | .jsonl, .ndjson | WikiANN, Universal NER |
| `BRAT` | .ann, .txt | LitBank |
| `JSON` | .json | MultiNERD |

## Task Types

```rust
pub enum Task {
    NER,              // Sequence labeling
    IntraDocCoref,    // Within-document coreference
    InterDocCoref,    // Cross-document coreference  
    NED,              // Entity Disambiguation / Linking
    RelationExtraction,
    EventExtraction,
    DiscontinuousNER, // CADEC, ShARe-style
    TemporalNER,      // Diachronic entities
    // ...
}
```

## Classical/Historical Language Datasets

For ancient/classical languages, use:
- `.historical()` builder method
- `Domain::Historical` or `Domain::Literary` as appropriate
- Appropriate ISO 639-3 codes: `sa` (Sanskrit), `grc` (Ancient Greek), `la` (Latin)

Key datasets for classical languages:
- **Mahānāma**: Sanskrit EDL, extreme name variation (arXiv:2509.19844)
- **NEReus**: Ancient Greek with deity types
- **HIPE-2022**: Multilingual historical NER

## Testing Datasets

```rust
#[test]
fn test_dataset_properties() {
    let ds = CustomDataset::new("test", Task::NER)
        .with_languages(&["en", "de"]);
    
    assert!(ds.supports_language("en"));
    assert!(ds.supports_task(Task::NER));
    assert!(ds.is_public()); // License allows redistribution
}
```
